Package com.duncpro.jroute.router

Class RouterResult<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.duncpro.jroute.router.RouterResult<E>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    RouterResult.Matched, RouterResult.MethodNotAllowed, RouterResult.ResourceNotFound
    public class RouterResult<E>
extends java.lang.Object
    There are three district types of RouterResult. 1. RouterResult.Matched, representing a successful match of a request to an endpoint. 2. RouterResult.ResourceNotFound, representing a failure to match the path to a resource. 3. RouterResult.MethodNotAllowed, representing a successful match of a request to a resource but a failure to match and the request method (http verb) to an endpoint on the resource.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Class Description
      static class  RouterResult.Matched<E>
      RouterResult representing the case where the given patch matched a resource within the Router, and the given HttpMethod is defined on that resource.
      static class  RouterResult.MethodNotAllowed<E>
      RouterResult representing the case where the given path matched a resource within the Router, but the given HttpMethod is not defined for the resource.
      static class  RouterResult.ResourceNotFound<E>
      RouterResult which indicates a failure to match the given path with any registered route.

    • Method Detail

      • asOptional

        public java.util.Optional<RouterResult.Matched<E>> asOptional()
        If this RouterResult is a successful matched (i.e. instanceof RouterResult.Matched), then this method returns an optional containing this object but cast to RouterResult.Matched. If this RouterResult is an error type, such as RouterResult.ResourceNotFound or RouterResult.MethodNotAllowed, then this method returns an empty optional.
